PN,38902
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F389A1784735286
OL,3,CPolice uncover one of Wiltshire's
OL,4,Clargest-ever cannabis farms
OL,6,FDetective Sergeant Joe Shanklin, who
OL,7,Fwas part of the search team, says that
OL,8,Fthe building "had been expertly
OL,9,Fmodified into a series of internal
OL,10,Frooms housing cannabis plants in
OL,11,Fvarying stages of maturity, from
OL,12,Fseedlings to established bushes."
OL,14,FHe added: "The sophisticated set up
OL,15,Fincluded electricity illegally drawn
OL,16,Fdirectly from the national grid to
OL,17,Fpower hundreds of grow lamps as well
OL,18,Fas a full irrigation system.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/4
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,390,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38903
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F389A1784735286
OL,3,CPolice uncover one of Wiltshire's
OL,4,Clargest-ever cannabis farms
OL,6,F"We have also found signs of a number
OL,7,Fof people who had been living on site,
OL,8,Fwith bedrooms and cooking facilities
OL,9,Fwithin the barn. The scale of this
OL,10,Foperation is significant and appears
OL,11,Fto have been in place for a
OL,12,Fsubstantial period of time."
OL,14,FThe factory was discovered by a member
OL,15,Fof the public on Friday 17th July.
OL,17,FPolice say engineers have disconnected
OL,18,Fthe "hazardous electricity supply and
OL,19,Fspecialist police search officers have
OL,20,Fbeen working methodically to log and
OL,21,Fremove the plants and equipment."
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/4
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
